Przyimków kierunku używamy, gdy wskazujemy kierunek, w którym ktoś lub cos się przemieszcza.
Są to m. in.:
over - (po)nad,
along- wzdłuż,
across - przez,
up- w górę,
down - w dół,
into- do,
out of- z,
round - zza (rogu),
za (rogiem),
onto - na,
through - (po)przez,
from ... to - z ... do.

The plane is flying over the city - Samolot leci nad miastem.
The car is going along the street. - Samochód jedzie ulicą.
The man is walking across the street.
- Mężczyzna przechodzi przez jezdnię.

The boy is going up the hill. - Chłopiec idzie pod górę.
The girl is going down the hill - Dziewczynka schodzi z pagórka.

The man is getting into the taxi. - Mężczyzna wsiada do taksówki.
The woman is getting out of the taxi. - Kobieta wysiada z taksówki.

The policeman is coming round the corner.
- Policjant wychodzi zza rogu.
The thief is jumping onto the truck.
- Złodziej wskakuje na ciężarówkę.

The bus is going through a tunnel. - Autobus przejeżdża przez tunel.
The bus is going from London to Oxford
-Autobus jedzie z Londynu do Oxfordu.

Uwaga:
Ze środkami lokomocji używamy najczęściej przyimka by.
Np. by car- samochodem,
by bus- autobusem,
by train- pociągiem,
by taxi- taksówką,
by plane - samolotem,
by boat- łódką.
ALE: on foot- na piechotę.

ćwiczenie 9
wstaw up, into, through, round, onto, from... to, over lub down.
1 The dog is jumping [...] the table.
2 The postman has just gone [...] the corner.
3 How far is it [...] your house [...] the post off ice?
4 The train is going [...] the tunnel.
5 The plane is flying [...] the village.
6 Look! That man has climbed [...] the ladder.
7 Tears are running [...] his face.
8 Come [...] the house and get warm.
1 onto
2 round 5 over
3 from ... to 6 up
4 through 7 down
8 into

ćwiczenie 10
Podkreśl właściwe przyimki.
1 You must go [up/across/into] the bridge to get to school.
2 Put the cake [into/out of/through] the oven.
3 The motorbike is going [down/onto/through] the tunnel.
4 The children ran [onto/out of/over] the classrooms when the bell rang.
5 I go to school [on/by/onto] foot.
6 The pop singer is ready to sing. He is coming [through/over /onto] the stage.
7 The child is running [through/over/across] the road.
8 The cat has jumped [down/onto/across] the car.
9 You must always take off your shoes when you come[into/down/round] the house.
10 He goes to work [by/ on/into] bus every day.
1 across
2 into 5 on
3 through 6 onto
4 out of 7 across
8 onto
9 into
10 by

ćwiczenie 11
Wstaw along, up, through, down, out of oraz across, a następnie powiedz, jak przejść z poczty na stację kolejową.
A: Excuse me. Where is the post office?
B: Go 1) [...] King's Road and go 2) [...] the tunnel.
When you come 3) [...] the tunnel, turn left. Walk until you
get to the bridge. Go 4) [...] the steps, 5)
the bridge and 6) [...] the steps. Then go 7) [...]
the road and the post office is in front of you.
1 along
2 through 4 up
3 out of 5 across
down
7 across





